               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210912-57-person546">
                  SAMUEL 
                  CHESTER
               <interp inst="t18210912-57-person546" type="surname" value="CHESTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210912-57-person546" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210912-57-person546" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in the Westminster-road. On the 5th of September, a little past one o'clock in the morning, I was at the foot of <placeName id="t18210912-57-crimeloc314">Blackfriars-bridge</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18210912-57-crimeloc314" type="placeName" value="Blackfriars-bridge"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18210912-57-crimeloc314" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210912-57-off312 t18210912-57-crimeloc314"></join>, on the London side, a gentleman said my handkerchief was gone - I felt, and missed it - I turned round, and saw the prisoner running as hard as could - I pursued, and only lost sight of him in turning the corner, and saw him throw it down in Water-street - a constable picked it up; I called Stop thief! and he was stopped without my losing-sight of him, except in turning the corner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210912-57-person547">
                  JOHN 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18210912-57-person547" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210912-57-person547" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210912-57-person547" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I joined in pursuit; I was sitting at the foot of the bridge; I lost sight of him only as he turned the corner - he threw the handkerchief down, and was secured; I searched and found a handkerchief in his hat, and a small knife and snuff box.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I know nothing at all about it.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18210912-57-verdict315" type="verdictDescription">
